{
"type": "fix",
"subject": "fix SubscriberSampler to correctly report the number of messages received",
"body": "The SubscriberSampler was incorrectly reporting the number of messages received. This commit fixes the issue by updating the result.setResponseMessage and result.setSampleCount methods to correctly report the number of messages received. The code lines 'result.setResponseMessage(loop + " messages received");' and 'result.setSampleCount(loop);' have been replaced with 'result.setResponseMessage(read + " messages received");' and 'result.setSampleCount(read);' respectively."
}

{
"type": "fix",
"subject": "Allow for minor variation in SampleResult#currentTimeInMillis() values",
"body": "The granularity of System.currentTimeMillis() - plus the fact that the nanoTime() offset is now calculated for each sampleResult - means that there can be some minor variation in the value returned by SampleResult#currentTimeInMillis().\n\nTo account for this, a fudge factor of 3ms is added to the comparison in the test. This should prevent false failures due to minor timing differences."
}

