{
"type": "fix",
"subject": "Fix file output stream in TestXSSFBugs",
"body": "The file output stream in TestXSSFBugs was not being properly handled. In the previous code, a file output stream was being used to write the workbook. However, this was not being closed properly. This could potentially lead to issues with the file being written. To fix this, the file output stream was replaced with a byte array output stream. This stream is automatically closed when it is garbage collected, which ensures that the file is properly written. Additionally, the NullOutputStream was used to write the workbook. This stream does not actually write the file, but it does not throw an exception when the stream is closed. This is useful for testing purposes."
}

